</caption>
<paragraph id="892436CFFFC4FFA8AA81FF777BE0FED9" blockId="11.[144,1101,166,317]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">abdominal tergites III–IV, and centre of V–VII brown; VIII yellowish brown. Bands on femora and tibiae more evident than in males; small brown macula present on venter of femora. Grasping comb absent. Abdominal segment VIII on the same plane as VII, with lateral margins divergent and posterior margin rounded. Genital segments exposed, globose, dark yellow.</paragraph>
