<collectingMunicipality id="6940ACB5FFC4FFA8AA81FC4A7AB8FC57" box="[144,188,923,947]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">The</collectingMunicipality>
term 
<taxonomicName id="4E9B4D4CFFC4FFA8AAEDFC4A7B64FC57" authorityName="Moreira &amp; Nessimian &amp; Rúdio &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2010" box="[252,352,923,947]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capixaba">
<emphasis id="BBEFEADDFFC4FFA8AAEDFC4A7B64FC57" box="[252,352,923,947]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">capixaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to natives of the 
<location id="8C446014FFC4FFA8A871FC4A789DFC57" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:013287D9FFC7FFAFAB79FBF37B28FED9:8C446014FFC4FFA8A871FC4A789DFC57" box="[608,665,923,947]" municipality="The" name="State" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770" stateProvince="Espirito Santo">State</location>
of 
<collectingRegion id="4B5FF82DFFC4FFA8A8AAFC4A795BFC57" box="[699,863,923,947]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, where the 
<typeStatus id="5620886DFFC4FFA8A9CBFC4D7E0EFC50" box="[986,1034,924,948]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">type</typeStatus>
series of the species was collected
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="892436CFFFC4FFA8AA81FBCA7B01FBD7" blockId="11.[144,261,1051,1075]" box="[144,261,1051,1075]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">
<emphasis id="BBEFEADDFFC4FFA8AA81FBCA7B01FBD7" box="[144,261,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="892436CFFFC4FFA8AA81FB937BA3FADE" blockId="11.[144,1101,1090,1689]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4E9B4D4CFFC4FFA8AB22FB957BB3FBBF" authority="Moreira &amp; Nessimian &amp; Rúdio &amp; Salles, 2010" authorityName="Moreira &amp; Nessimian &amp; Rúdio &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2010" box="[307,439,1091,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capixaba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BBEFEADDFFC4FFA8AB22FB957BB3FBBF" box="[307,439,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">P. capixaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A0DC57A6FFC4FFA8ABD3FB92781EFBBE" box="[450,538,1091,1114]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be diagnosed by the body and legs densely covered by long thin setae (
<figureCitation id="11A02A4AFFC4FFA8ABC3FBB37848FB9E" box="[466,588,1122,1146]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[213,280,1564,1586]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,161,1530]" captionTargetId="figure-5@10.[213,1170,161,1531]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Paravelia capixaba sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; male. (B) Head and pronotum; arrow shows circular punctuation; male. (C) Part of thorax; arrow shows circular punctuation on mesoacetabulum; ventrolateral view; male. (D) Fore leg; arrow shows tibial grasping comb; lateral view; male. (E) Proctiger; lateral view; male. (F) Paramere; lateral view; male. (G) Paramere; laterocaudal view; male. (H) Dorsal habitus; female. Scale bar 1.00 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5212109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5212109/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
); antennomere III longer than I; absence of tubercles on thoracic sternites (
<figureCitation id="11A02A4AFFC4FFA8ABE7FB53786FFB7E" box="[502,619,1154,1178]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[213,280,1564,1586]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,161,1530]" captionTargetId="figure-5@10.[213,1170,161,1531]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Paravelia capixaba sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; male. (B) Head and pronotum; arrow shows circular punctuation; male. (C) Part of thorax; arrow shows circular punctuation on mesoacetabulum; ventrolateral view; male. (D) Fore leg; arrow shows tibial grasping comb; lateral view; male. (E) Proctiger; lateral view; male. (F) Paramere; lateral view; male. (G) Paramere; laterocaudal view; male. (H) Dorsal habitus; female. Scale bar 1.00 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5212109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5212109/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
) (the mesoacetabulum is produced on the inner portion of the ventral surface, but not developed into a tubercle like in members of 
<taxonomicName id="4E9B4D4CFFC4FFA8AAFAFB1378C1FB3E" authority="Polhemus and Polhemus, 1993" authorityName="Polhemus and Polhemus" authorityYear="1993" box="[235,709,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Platyvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BBEFEADDFFC4FFA8AAFAFB137B5EFB3E" box="[235,346,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">Platyvelia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="ED0A4B3EFFC4FFA8AB72FB1378C1FB3E" author="Polhemus JT &amp; Polhemus DA" box="[355,709,1218,1242]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770" pagination="391 - 398" refId="ref23038" refString="Polhemus JT, Polhemus DA. 1993. Two new genera for New World Veliinae (Heteroptera: Veliidae). J N Y Entomol Soc. 101 (3): 391 - 398." type="journal article" year="1993">Polhemus and Polhemus, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
); trochanters and femora without spines, tibiae with a ventral row of black acute spinules throughout their length (
<figureCitation id="11A02A4AFFC4FFA8AA89FAD37B17FAFE" box="[152,275,1282,1306]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[213,280,1564,1586]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,161,1530]" captionTargetId="figure-5@10.[213,1170,161,1531]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Paravelia capixaba sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; male. (B) Head and pronotum; arrow shows circular punctuation; male. (C) Part of thorax; arrow shows circular punctuation on mesoacetabulum; ventrolateral view; male. (D) Fore leg; arrow shows tibial grasping comb; lateral view; male. (E) Proctiger; lateral view; male. (F) Paramere; lateral view; male. (G) Paramere; laterocaudal view; male. (H) Dorsal habitus; female. Scale bar 1.00 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5212109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5212109/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
); male proctiger without central projections, and the shape of the male paramere (
<figureCitation id="11A02A4AFFC4FFA8AB18FAF37B9EFADE" box="[265,410,1314,1338]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="10.[213,280,1564,1586]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,161,1530]" captionTargetId="figure-5@10.[213,1170,161,1531]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 3. Paravelia capixaba sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; male. (B) Head and pronotum; arrow shows circular punctuation; male. (C) Part of thorax; arrow shows circular punctuation on mesoacetabulum; ventrolateral view; male. (D) Fore leg; arrow shows tibial grasping comb; lateral view; male. (E) Proctiger; lateral view; male. (F) Paramere; lateral view; male. (G) Paramere; laterocaudal view; male. (H) Dorsal habitus; female. Scale bar 1.00 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5212109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5212109/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">Figure 3F,G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="892436CFFFC4FFA8AAAAFA937B37F9DD" blockId="11.[144,1101,1090,1689]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770">
Based on original descriptions, 
<taxonomicName id="4E9B4D4CFFC4FFA8A809FA927893FABE" authority="Moreira &amp; Nessimian &amp; Rúdio &amp; Salles, 2010" authorityName="Moreira &amp; Nessimian &amp; Rúdio &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2010" box="[536,663,1346,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2770" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capixaba" status="sp. nov.">
